title: Educated migrants can make Europe‘s job market more vibrant: Linas Linkevicius
summary: Lithuania which had recently assumed the Presidency of the Council of the European Union says European values is about helping refugees fleeing war or persecution but has warned that economic migrants should not be allowed to piggy back on genuine refugees and enter Europe.

title: UK to take in 20,000 Syrian refugees over the next five years
summary: A wave of compassion across Britain is seeing thousands of British families volunteer to host Syrian refugees in their homes as prime minister David Cameron finally announced that UK will admit 20,000 Syrian refugees over the next five years.

title: Top British minister to arrive in Delhi on Sept 11 to plan Modi trip to UK in November
summary: Conservative Party's rising star and British prime minister David Cameron's most trusted - Sajid Javid, is coming to India this week as UK starts preparations for Narendra Modi's maiden visit to London this November.

title: Hate crimes in London have increased by over 7o% in just over a year
summary: Hate crimes in London have increased by over 7o% in just over a year, 60% of victims being women wearing a headscarf or a hijab.

title: Habre forced into dock as Senegal war crimes trial resumes
summary: Chad's former dictator Hissene Habre was forced into the dock after refusing to attend the resumption of his trial in Senegal on Monday for war crimes and other atrocities.

title: Police question 2 Indians in Thai bombing case
summary: Two Indians have been taken into custody for questioning after they were seen on CCTV talking to a foreign suspect wanted in Thailand's deadliest bombing at a temple here while a person arrested in the case told police that the mastermind of the attack had fled the country.

title: IS captures oil field in central Syria
summary: Activists say members of the Islamic State group have captured an oil field in central Syria.

title: Scentists discover a new Stonehenge, hidden underground for centuries
summary: Non-invasive X-rays and remote sensing technologies have stumbled upon a major discovery beneath Durrington Walls – home to England's most visited archeological find – the Stonehenge.

title: British scientists discover blood test that tells how old your body is against chronological age
summary: How old are you? No, not how long you have lived but how old is your body actually?

title: US dentist who killed Cecil the lion breaks silence
summary: The US dentist who killed Zimbabwe's Cecil the lion has broken weeks of silence, saying in an interview that he had no idea it was a special feline and announcing he would return to work after lying low.

title: Three militants killed in Pakistan's first drone strike in North Waziristan
summary: Pakistan Army on Monday claimed to have killed three suspected militants in Shawal valley of North Waziristan tribal region on the border with Afghanistan in its first ever air strike by a locally manufactured unmanned drone aircraft, named "Burraq".

title: Cold or hot start, we are ready
summary: In what appeared apparently to be a response to recent claim of Indian army chief that his troops were ready for the "swift, short nature of future wars", Pakistan's army chief Raheel Sharif on Sunday said that his forces were fully prepared to thwart any external aggression.

title: Greek ferry saves 61 migrants as 2,500 arrive in Athens
summary: A Greek passenger ferry today sent its lifeboats to rescue 61 migrants whose boat was at risk of sinking off the island of Lesbos, port police said.

title: Refugee crisis: Hollande says France will take 24,000 refugees and 'begin Syria air missions'
summary: Francois Hollande has said France will welcome 24,000 refugees as part of an EU-wide plan that "can and will" bring the crisis under control.

title: Iran foreign minister Mohammad Javad Zarif criticizes calls for ouster of Syria's Assad
summary: Iran's foreign minister on Monday criticized demands for the resignation of Syrian president Bashar Assad, saying such calls have prolonged the Arab country's civil war.

title: Qatar deploys 1,000 ground troops to fight Yemen's rebels
summary: Monday's development, which was also reported by the Qatar-based and funded Al-Jazeera news network, marks the first time Qatari ground troops are known to have been deployed to battle the rebels, known as Houthis.

title: Two Indians taken into custody in Thai bombing case
summary: Two Indians have been taken into custody for questioning by Thai police after they were seen on CCTVs talking to a foreign suspect wanted in Thailand's deadliest bombing at a Brahma temple here, a media report said today.

title: Chinese woman must choose between 2nd child, husband's job
summary: A public outcry has been raised over the plight of a 41-year-old woman who's considering an illegal abortion at 8 months because the child would violate China's restrictive birth policy and would cost her husband his government job.

title: France to take 24,000 migrants under EU refugee plan: Hollande
summary: "This is a crisis, and it is a grave and dramatic one. It can be brought under control and it will be," Hollande said.

title: France sending reconnaissance flights over Syria against IS
summary: President Francois Hollande says terror attacks have been planned from Syria against several countries, including France.
